"description": "Boston Review was created in response to the growing demand for high quality GRE preparation course. As anyone who has prepared for these exams will agree
column2: one of the biggest problems with preparing for the test is the lack of sufficient top-quality teaching methodology
column3: more so in case of students who are preparing by paying huge tuition fees at so called \"premium test prep institutes\". \n\nThese institutes develop general curricula aimed at a broad population
column4: the so called \"average students.\" They do not tailor their curricula based on student needs because customization is expensive and time-consuming. We believe that a tailored program is a basic prerequisite for any effective tutoring relationship
column5: particularly with GRE students who are often juggling multiple priorities. We build each tutoring relationship around a unique student and we only work with students on a one-on-one basis. Between each class
column6: we scrutinize student progress section-by-section and problem-by-problem. This is something that no other test prep company has been able to do.\n\nOur mission is to provide top quality teaching with ample practice and reference material. We guarantee that our curriculum is very strongly correlated with the questions you are most likely to see and the concepts tested on the actual GRE test."
